abstract: President Trump is expected to sign it into law as part of the overall spending package. Some advocates warn that more action is needed to reduce teenage vaping of e-cigarettes.
snippet: President Trump is expected to sign it into law as part of the overall spending package. Some advocates warn that more action is needed to reduce teenage vaping of e-cigarettes.
lead_paragraph: The House and Senate have now passed a provision that would ban the sale of tobacco and e-cigarettes to anyone under 21, at a time when Congress and the Trump administration are facing public pressure to reduce the soaring rates of teenage vaping.

abstract: A conservative talk-radio outlet in Denver canceled a married couple’s show after the husband wished on the air for something to draw attention away from impeachment.
snippet: A conservative talk-radio outlet in Denver canceled a married couple’s show after the husband wished on the air for something to draw attention away from impeachment.
lead_paragraph: The conservative married couple’s afternoon talk show on KNUS in Denver had been going for a half-hour on Tuesday when the husband made a remark that alarmed his wife, stunned their listeners — and soon cost them their jobs.

abstract: Some farm groups and farm-state lawmakers expressed anger at the Trump administration Thursday over final ethanol rules that they said failed to uphold the president’s promises to the industry.
snippet: Some farm groups and farm-state lawmakers expressed anger at the Trump administration Thursday over final ethanol rules that they said failed to uphold the president’s promises to the industry.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES, Iowa — Some farm groups and farm-state lawmakers expressed anger at the Trump administration Thursday over final ethanol rules that they said failed to uphold the president’s promises to the industry.
headline_main: Farm, Ethanol Groups Angered at Final EPA Ethanol Rule
headline_print_headline: Farm, Ethanol Groups Angered at Final EPA Ethanol Rule

abstract: With government funding set to lapse Friday, the Senate passed the $1.4 trillion deal in time for lawmakers to leave for a scheduled holiday break.
snippet: With government funding set to lapse Friday, the Senate passed the $1.4 trillion deal in time for lawmakers to leave for a scheduled holiday break.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Congress gave final approval on Thursday to $1.4 trillion in federal spending, staving off a lapse in government funding for the remainder of the fiscal year and delivering the legislation to President Trump in a year-end flurry of bipartisan compromise.

lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — A New York judge denied the U.S. government's request Thursday to toss out a lawsuit challenging the constitutionality of Immigration and Customs Enforcement arrests in New York courthouses.
